==English==
===Noun===
[[Category:English nouns]]
'''larboard'''

# {{obsolete}} The left side of a ship, looking from the [[stern]].

====Usage notes====
In the British Navy it was not until 1844 that ''larboard'' was abandoned for ''[[port]]'' in reference to that side of the ship.  The term ''port'' however had always been used when referring to the [[helm]] (ie. sailing direction), in order to avoid any confusion between ''starboard'' and ''larboard'' in such an important matter.  (Reference: [[w:Ray Parkin|Ray Parkin]], ''H. M. Bark Endeavour'', [[w:Miegunyah Press|Miegunyah Press]], second edition 2003, ISBN 0-522-85093-6, page 56.)

